18054807,0.08596800,0.01025204,0.04343133,-0.04566603,0.03481261,0.02992390,0.01459271,0.02623349,0.02291938,0.04876662,-0.01026752,-0.02320824,-0.05234426,0.02803899,0.03812204,0.02436633,-0.02511050,-0.01485521,-0.01268706,0.01431018,-0.05277133,0.03458468,-0.04502480,-0.01882181,-0.01518182,-0.07484816,0.00138545,0.01451373,-0.02106362,-0.01949938,-0.04018001,0.02245246,0.05379945,0.00306462,-0.03553799,0.01555947,0.03999555,0.07967657,-0.03150342,-0.00992216,-0.03362062,-0.01507776]',E'ReadResource\n\nAlthough Terraform typically expects to have exclusive control over any remote\nobject that is bound to a resource instance, in practice users may make changes\nto those objects outside of Terraform, causing Terraform''s records of the\nobject to become stale.\n\nThe `ReadResource` function asks the provider to make a best effort to detect\nany such external changes and describe them so that Terraform Core can use\nan up-to-date **Prior State** as the input to the next `PlanResourceChange`\ncall.','{"source": "terraform", "version": "1.9", "language": "hcl", "title": "Terraform Resource Instance Change Lifecycle", "section_title": "resource-instance-change-lifecycle", "url": "https://github.com/hashicorp/terraform/blob/main/docs/resource-instance-change-lifecycle.md", "topics": "terraform,iac,resource,instance,change,lifecycle", "categories": "devops,infrastructure,cloud"}');
